  "prompt": "What is the limit to follow in Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram has set limits on the number of accounts you can follow to prevent spam and misuse. Typically, the maximum number of accounts one can follow is 7,500. However, for new accounts or accounts that have been flagged for suspicious activity, this limit may be lower. \n\nInstagram also has other engagement limits, such as the number of likes, comments, and direct messages you can send in a given time period to help manage spam and promote genuine interactions.\n\nKeep in mind that these limits can change, so it's always a good idea to check Instagram's official guidelines or resources for the most current information.",
